<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id128bd9b4-f87d-11ef-b94d-97e317d2120c" identifier="/us/usc/t4/s109"><num value="109">§ 109.</num><heading> Same; exception of Indians</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Nothing in sections 105 and 106 of this title shall be deemed to authorize the levy or collection of any tax on or from any Indian not otherwise taxed.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id128bd9b5-f87d-11ef-b94d-97e317d2120c">(<ref href="/us/act/1947-07-30/ch389">July 30, 1947, ch. 389</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/61/645">61 Stat. 645</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
